      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To: All Relevant Parties\n\nSubject: Enhanced Know Your Customer (KYC) Onboarding Process\n\n1. Introduction:\nIn accordance with the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA), the USA PATRIOT Act, and other applicable anti-money laundering (AML) regulations, our institution is committed to implementing a rigorous onboarding process to verify the beneficial ownership of our customers and ensure compliance with relevant regulatory requirements. This memo outlines the enhanced KYC procedures to ensure compliance with the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN) guidelines and relevant regulatory standards.\n\n2. Customer Identification Program (CIP):\nOur CIP is designed to identify and verify the beneficial ownership of our customers, including but not limited to:\n- Government-issued identification documents (e.g., passport, driver's license, state ID) that demonstrate the customer's identity and proof of name\n- Proof of address documents (e.g., utility bill, lease agreement, bank statement) that establish the customer's physical presence and residence\n- Other supporting documentation as required by applicable laws and regulations, including but not limited to:\n  * Beneficial ownership information, as defined by the Corporate Transparency Act (CTA) and the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n  * Politically",
